cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.MM, cs.SI 

This paper discusses the impact of traffic mix on caching performance in a content-centric network, which is a topic related to network infrastructure and communication protocols. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the efficiency of caching different types of content, which could fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as well. Additionally, the paper evaluates the performance of cache hierarchy, which could be related to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also discusses the caching of video on demand, which could be related to cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
